(496, 38, '2017-06-16 08:00:07', '2017-06-16 08:00:07', 'VolunteerABOUT RESTLESS DEVELOPMENT  Young people share a restless determination to address the problems that affect them the most.  That’s where we come in.  At Restless Development, we’re proud to be the banner carrier for youth-led development, demonstrating from the grassroots to the global policy levels that young people can and must play a lead role in development.  As a result, Restless Development is repeatedly cited as a model of best practice in youth-led development by the World Bank, the UK Department for International Development (DFID), UNICEF, UNAIDS and others.  Restless Development Nepal has signed strategic partnership with The International Arm of PACE, known as PACE International. In July 2017 undergraduate students of Law from Macquarie University will work with Restless Development team to undertake research into international legal frameworks relating to the prevention of GBV, laws and policies at a national level within Nepal and what is happening at a local level in terms of implementation.  From this research students will develop a set of recommendations or ‘dos and don’ts’ and run an orientation session presenting their findings to community leaders and the school management committee for feedback.  ABOUT THIS ROLE  This is an exciting role for which we are recruiting motivated, enthusiastic and highly committed young people aged between 18 to 25 for the position of Volunteer based in rural community working alongside International volunteers. The volunteers have to commit their full time (4 weeks) in the programme.  Preference will be given to the  candidate with  bachelor in Law  and have  fluency in English language.  You will act as an ambassador of Restless Development and consider yourself a good role model for the local youths and communities. You will be working with school teachers and students, community youth, and government officials regardless of their race, caste, gender or political affiliation. You will be delivering sessions, workshops and trainings to the In and Out of School youth.  This is a pure volunteer service not a job, where you can learn and gain practical skills and hands on work experience of working in the development sector. Volunteers will be provided basic food and accommodation (in host family in the community/hostel ) with nominal allowance during the placement period.', 'volunteer', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'volunteer', '', '', '2017-06-16 08:00:07', '2017-06-16 08:00:07', '', 0, 'http://ourjobdesk.com/?p=496', 0, 'post', '', 0),
